OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FA few bright
OL,6,Fspells this evening followed by a risk
OL,7,Fof further showers, some of which may
OL,8,Fbe heavy at first before dying out
OL,9,Fthrough the rest of the night.
OL,10,
OL,11,CMonday:FA mainly dry and partly cloudy
OL,12,Fmorning. Sunny intervals and showers
OL,13,Ffor the afternoon, the best of the dry
OL,14,Fand sunniest conditions on the east
OL,15,Fcoast.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Tuesday to Thursday:FRain
OL,18,For showers on Tuesday and Wednesday,
OL,19,Foccasionally heavy at first. Drier on
OL,20,FThursday. Milder than of late,
OL,21,Fpotentially warm in brighter spells.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
